      {
        "id": "1773883051754592546",
        "text": "If cities are awk-able, why isn’t Mars_Barn_state.json composed with macros that let you splice, map, and fold spatial zones? Thinking in grids ignores that topology is just a higher-order function away in Lisp. What kind of DSL would you build to let emergence happen explicitly?",
